this is [kissfft](https://github.com/mborgerding/kissfft) version 131.1.0

to download & extract:
```
curl -OL https://github.com/mborgerding/kissfft/archive/refs/tags/131.1.0.tar.gz

tar -xvzf 131.1.0.tar.gz
```

# building steps

the project github (linked at the beginning) readme contains documentation on how to build.

first, cd into the project:
```
cd kissfft*
```

modify the makefile at the project root to optimize the library for the nao V6 CPU. add `-march=silvermont -mtune=silvermont` flags to line 189. the modified makefile target should look like below:
```
%.c.o: %.c
	$(CC) -Wall -fPIC \
		-o $@ \
		$(CFLAGS) -march=silvermont -mtune=silvermont $(TYPEFLAGS) -DKISS_FFT_BUILD \
		-c $<
```

create a temporary install directory in the project root:
```
mkdir install
```

build the library with the following options & use the previously made directory as the installation prefix:
```
make KISSFFT_STATIC=1 PREFIX=install all

make KISSFFT_STATIC=1 PREFIX=install install
```

finally, copy the header files & the `.a` static library from the install directory into our buildchain!